ng oral castor oil was associated with a higher likelihood of initiation of labour compared to the placebo group [A33050]. Castor oil is known to induce diarrhea, and has been used in studies to assess anti-diarrheal effect of some compounds [F70]. ', 'DrugBank', 0, 0, 0);
